cs.CL, cs.AI, cs.IR, cs.LG, cs.NE 

This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category cs.CL (Computation and Language) as it deals with natural language processing and specifically document summarization. It could also belong to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) as it uses a neural network model for summarization. Additionally, it could be categorized under cs.IR (Information Retrieval) as summarization is a common task in this field. The use of user preferences and control variables could also make it relevant to cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
